criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Active TB defined as either a) microbiologically confirmed TB (sputum AFB smear
             positive by microscopy or +GeneXpert at entry) or b) clinical TB that is subsequently
             confirmed by Acid-Fast Bacilli (AFB) culture;

          -  with or without concurrent HIV infection)

          -  initiating TB therapy;

          -  age ≥ 18 years of age;

          -  AUDIT Score ≥ 8 in men /≥4 in women.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  already in treatment for unhealthy alcohol use;

          -  unable to participate in intervention sessions either due to severity of medical
             illness, cognitive dysfunction or active psychosis;

          -  pregnant (will refer directly to alcohol treatment);

          -  household member of current study participant;
